post_text:
Navasota ISD Parents/Guardians -

We are almost to the end of our 3rd week of instruction and our 3-week progress report. Our faculty and staff have worked tirelessly to bring instruction to our students both in person and remotely.

Friday, September 25th, will be the last day for parents and students to make the change to on-campus learning until Tuesday, October 20th, which is the beginning of the 2nd 9-weeks. After next Friday, students would not be permitted to transfer to on-campus learning until the end of the 9-week grading period.

If you wish to return to on-campus learning, please contact your students campus to arrange for this change as soon as possible.

Parents can check student grades by logging into Skyward. This and other parent links are available at https://www.navasotaisd.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=140233&type=d&pREC_ID=473872

#WeAreNavasota #TogetherWeCan #LearningLeadingSucceeding

Navasota ISD
June 1 at 6:18 PM 路

PSA for our Parents: SNAP Food Benefits for Eligible Students
Recognizing that COVID-19 has been challenging for many families and has put a strain on household food budgets, the U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) has approved a new, $1 billion benefit program to help eligible families buy food during the coronavirus pandemic. Through the program, households will receive a one-time benefit of up to $285 per eligible child. All Texas schools are being asked to share Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) information with eligible families, so families understand how to receive benefits. The online application that families must submit will be active the first week of June and close on June 30. Get the details by clicking the link below.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1lFDP58TEkasiAvL9vLEYljEFA05iSRlg/view?usp=sharing

ATTENTION STUDENT ATHLETES!

Strength and conditioning workouts have started. Here are some reminders:

You must bring your own water. Athletics is not allowed to hand out water bottles due to COVID-19.
If you are having any symptoms of COVID-19 or are feeling ill, please stay at home.

Reminder for parents: PHYSICAL DAY is Thursday, July 30th at 1pm. You are required to get a physical if:
You are going into 7th grade in 2020-2021
You were injured this year and required a physicians clearance for that injury
You are new to athletics in 2020-2021.

If anyone has specific questions regarding physicals/eligibility for next year, please email Ryan Attridge at attridger@navasotaisd.org

Navasota ISD
June 1 at 6:18 PM 路

PSA for our Parents: SNAP Food Benefits for Eligible Students
Recognizing that COVID-19 has been challenging for many families and has put a strain on household food budgets, the U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) has approved a new, $1 billion benefit program to help eligible families buy food during the coronavirus pandemic. Through the program, households will receive a one-time benefit of up to $285 per eligible child. All Texas schools are being asked to share Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) information with eligible families, so families understand how to receive benefits. The online application that families must submit will be active the first week of June and close on June 30. Get the details by clicking the link below.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1lFDP58TEkasiAvL9vLEYljEFA05iSRlg/view?usp=sharing

post_text: Navasota ISD will begin the Summer Feeding Program on June 1st and run through July 17th. Summer Feeding will run Monday through Friday from 10:00 am until 12:00 noon at the curbside of the John C. Webb Elementary Cafeteria. Grab and Go breakfast and lunch will be made available to all students ages 0-18. Students will need to be present to receive the meals. Delivery of meals by bus will not be available during the summer. We will be closed the week of June 29 through July 3 for the 4th of July Holiday. #WeAreNavasota

post_text: Congratulations Navasota FFA! #LearningLeadingSucceeding
shared_text:
Navasota FFA
May 30 at 10:59 PM 路

The Navasota FFA breeding heifer exhibitors all did a great job today and placed very well. Demi Harrington has a tremendous day winning the intermediate showmanship contest, Champion Santa Gertrudis, and Supreme Champion the show as well as Reserve Champion Commercial heifer. Rhett Harrington, Kaden Leonard and Kelton Leonard all also placed well in the Santa Gertrudis breed. Cullen and Dlynn Robbins did well in the Beefmaster show and Kaelee Gosse did extremely well in the British division being named Reserve Division Champion.

NISD SHARES GRADUATION PLANS FOR NHS AND BIZZELL ACADEMY:

NAVASOTA HIGH SCHOOL GRADUATION PLANS:
Navasota High School has made plans for graduation. It is our goal to honor our graduates in the most traditional way while following the guidelines provided by Governor Abbott and the Texas Education Agency. *Please be aware that this plan is subject to change if restrictions are increased or decreased by the state.

Graduation Guidelines 2020 can be found here: https://bit.ly/NISD2020grad
Please click the link above to view TEA Guidelines as well as a link to choose your ceremony.

Special Military Graduation - Tuesday, June 2nd, at 8:00 pm
Graduation #1 - Thursday, July 23rd, at 8:00 pm
Graduation #2 - Friday, July 24th, at 8:00 pm
Graduation #3 - Saturday, July 25th, at 10:00 am
Graduation #4 - Saturday, July 25th, at 8:00 pm

W.B. BIZZELL GRADUATION PLANS:
Date: August 13th
Place: NELC Outdoors
Time: TBD
*If guidelines change by August, the graduation ceremony will be moved indoors.

post_text:
PSA for our Parents: SNAP Food Benefits for Eligible Students
Recognizing that COVID-19 has been challenging for many families and has put a strain on household food budgets, the U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) has approved a new, $1 billion benefit program to help eligible families buy food during the coronavirus pandemic. Through the program, households will receive a one-time benefit of up to $285 per eligible child. All Texas schools are being asked to share Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) information with eligible families, so families understand how to receive benefits. The online application that families must submit will be active the first week of June and close on June 30. Get the details by clicking the link below. #WeAreNavasota #TogetherWeCan

https://tea.texas.gov/about-tea/news-and-multimedia/correspondence/taa-letters/p-ebt-overview-and-communications-toolkit

post_text: Last chance to get your instrument!
shared_text:
NHS Rattler Band
April 30 at 11:45 PM 路

Mr. Williams and Mr. England will both be at the band hall tomorrow morning. We thought we were done moving stuff, but theres a few more things we missed. If your personal instrument is still at the band hall, it must be picked up tomorrow or it stays over the summer. There will be some construction going on in the band hall to help with the sound proofing between us and choir, and Its likely to get dusty and hot in there when they turn off the power for construction. 9-11 am.

post_text:
Attention Parents of Rattler Athletes!

Athletic (UIL) forms will be completed online for the 2020-2021 school year. To complete these forms for your student athlete, go to the website below. You can create an account to have access to the forms once they are completed, but it is not required (just click continue as a guest when prompted).

https://navasotaisd.rankonesport.com/New/NewInstructionsPage.aspx

In regards to physical exams, the UIL is discussing options for the 2020-2021 school year. As soon as we know anything we will let you know.

If you have questions on this process, please email attridger@navasotaisd.org or pennartza@navasotaisd.org. Thank you!

Goodwin Lasiter Strong
April 21 at 1:27 PM 路

Turf and track replacement at Navasota ISD is rolling at full force as Hellas Construction is set to complete installation of the new football and soccer field turf before NISDs May graduation. With good weather and better luck we may even have the new grey track and scoreboard installed in time too! The stone drainage layer is regraded, track camera boxes are installed, and the field is being prepared for the E-Layer safety pad installation today and the turf carpet installation next week.

post_text: 2020 NHS Graduation Information
shared_text:
Navasota High School
April 20 at 11:57 PM 路

To the 2020 Senior Class of Navasota High School, their families, and their friends -
Navasota High School and Navasota ISD would like to announce that, unless prohibited by further developments in the COVID-19 pandemic, we have rescheduled the May 29th graduation ceremony to July 24, 2020, at 8:00 p.m. at Rattler Stadium. It is our hope that we are able to come together to celebrate the accomplishments of the class of 2020 with a traditional graduation ceremony if at all possible. If the pandemic restrictions are not lifted by that time, then we will plan for a non-traditional celebration to do what we can to make it special for our graduating Seniors and their families. Please continue to check the Navasota ISD website and follow us on social media for updates. #WeAreNavasota #Classof2020 #RattlerNation

post_text:
Notice is hereby given that a Regular Board Meeting of the Board of Trustees of the Navasota ISD will be held on April 20, 2020, beginning at 6:30 PM.
Note to Public of Video Conferencing: Pursuant to Governor Abbotts Temporary Suspension of Open Meetings Laws issued on March 16, 2020 to advance the public health
goal of limiting face-to-face meetings (also called social distancing), this meeting will be conducted via video conference, which will be audible to the Board and public and allow for two-way communication. The Board President, presiding officer or trustees will not be physically present at one location but a quorum will be required for the video conference meeting. More information about public access can be found in the document below. #WeAreNavasota

.https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OZeuuIHkdz4GHulBr0nuSqx0wGDCwoK0/view?usp=sharing

Parents who wish to access student grades can do so by the following:
Go to www.navasotaisd.org
Click on the QUICKLINKS tab at top upper right corner
Choose Family Access Gradebook
Login ID: lastname.firstname (this could be in the name of the father or mother, so you may have to try both)
Password: password
You will be prompted to change the password upon first login
If you have changed your password previously and have forgotten it, click the Forgot Login/Password link.
If you get locked out, you will need to fill out the following form to have it unlocked. bit.ly/NISDlockedout

#LearningLeadingSucceeding #WeAreNavasota

Navasota High School: NATIONAL HONOR SOCIETY UPDATE
Navasota High School National Honor Society eligible applicants were emailed this morning with updated information in order to submit their applications online. If you know an eligible student, please have them check their emails for more information. If they did not receive an email and feel that they were supposed to, please email Mrs. Stanley at stanleye@navasotaisd.org. National Honor Society applications are now due April 17th online, but will be accepted later for students that do not have access to technology at home. For students that submit the application by April 17th, decision letters will be sent out on May 1st. National Honor Society inductions will be postponed until the Fall semester. Please reach out to Mrs. Stanley with any questions that you may have. #TogetherWeCan #LearningLeadingSucceeding #WeAreNavasota

post_text: Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately. #TogetherWeCan #WeAreNavasota

post_text:
Navasota High School: NATIONAL HONOR SOCIETY UPDATE
Navasota High School National Honor Society eligible applicants were emailed this morning with updated information in order to submit their applications online. If you know an eligible student, please have them check their emails for more information. If they did not receive an email and feel that they were supposed to, please email Mrs. Stanley at stanleye@navasotaisd.org. National Honor Society applications are now due April 17th online, but will be accepted later for students that do not have access to technology at home. For students that submit the application by April 17th, decision letters will be sent out on May 1st. National Honor Society inductions will be postponed until the Fall semester. Please reach out to Mrs. Stanley with any questions that you may have. #TogetherWeCan #LearningLeadingSucceeding #WeAreNavasota

shared_text:
Navasota High School
April 6 at 1:26 AM 路

Hey Rattlers!

Teachers will have new work (low tech packets) available for pick up on Wednesday, April 8 from 10-12 at Webb and Highpoint. Please bring a piece of paper with your schedule to get your packets. These will be 2 weeks worth of work and the next pickup date wont be until April 22.

Packets can be printed here: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1jRjW97wwiKWVLvw1rdFaGhnVFpMA4pHD

Please email your teacher if you have questions or need help.

Freshman need to email schedule requests to Mrs. Spikerman this week or she will choose your classes for you.

If you owe attendance hours from the fall, get your hours sheets to Mr. Wesley.

All students need to participate in learning opportunities to get credit for this semester.

Watch for more information in your email this week. Thanks to everyone that is working hard to take care of business!

post_text:
After discussions with local and state authorities, Navasota ISD will remain closed through April 10. We, along with many other area school districts, have come to this decision in an abundance of caution for our students, staff, and our community.

We will continue to serve Grab and Go meals at both Webb Elementary and High Point Elementary through this closure.

Our hope and plan at this time would be a staff work day on Monday, April 13th, with students returning on Tuesday, April 14th. We will continue to monitor the situation and make any updates as needed.

#WeAreNavasota #TogetherWeCan

shared_text:
Navasota ISD
March 23 at 1:49 AM 路

AT HOME LEARNING OPTIONS NOW AVAILABLE
At Home Learning will be available beginning Monday, March 23. To access instructional lessons online, please use this link:

https://bit.ly/navasotaisdathomelearning2020

Parents who prefer a low-tech option can download the printable version themselves, or if a printer is not available, they can request a packet during lunch pick up times at Webb Elementary and High Point Elementary beginning Monday, March 23rd.

These resources are to help you as parents help your students during this time in which our students are not able to be at school. We are here to serve you. Take care of your family during this time!

#WeAreNavasota #LearningLeadingSucceeding #TogetherWeCan

shared_text:
Navasota Examiner
March 20 at 4:25 PM 路

IMMEDIATE RELEASE FROM THE CITY OF NAVASOTA:
The City of Navasota is urging residents to be mindful of the juvenile curfew ordinance. Any person 17 years of age or younger is not to be out, without a parent, later than 11:00 PM Sunday through Thursday, and 11:59 PM Friday through Saturday.

Failure to comply with the curfew ordinance could result in a citation to the minor and any parent who knowingly allowed the minor to be out unsupervised.

Work, school and church functions are possible exceptions to the ordinance.

Please contact Navasota City Hall at (936)825-6475 with any questions

NISD Family and Rattler Nation:
Navasota ISD is continuing to monitor the current situation regarding COVID-19, or Coronavirus, and is in contact with our local Grimes County Emergency Management authorities.

We are also getting daily updates and we are awaiting additional information from the Texas Education Agency and the Commissioner of Education as it will assist us in making decisions over the next couple of days.

The safety of our students and staff is always a top priority for Navasota ISD and we thank you for your patience as we continue to gather necessary information to make the best decision for our students, staff, and our community.

Posted: 2/12/20 at 8:56 a.m.
Navasota High School received a bomb threat early this morning and is currently investigating whether the threat is credible. Students have been evacuated and we are currently working with Navasota Police and the Navasota Fire Department. For their safety, students are not allowed to leave at this time. We will post more information as it becomes available.

LAUNCHING THE NEXT GENERATION
Education is the foundation upon which we build our future."--Christine Gregoire
Tuesday evening NISD past and present Board Members were honored before the monthly Board Meeting with a meal and some time to visit and reminisce. The present Board members agreed that the foundation and goals set by previous Navasota ISD Boards is a driving force for our present School Board. Thank you to each of these former Board Members, as well as those unable to attend for helping us build the future! #WeAreNavasota

NHS PROM NEWS
The NHS Prom for Juniors & Seniors and guests, A Starry Night in the 20's, is Saturday, April 25, 2020 at The Brazos Center in Bryan from 8PM until Midnight.
Tickets are on sale in the NHS Library for $50 each until the end of February. Tickets include a souvenir t-shirt and a souvenir keychain.
There is a fundraiser February 3-14 selling tumblers to pay for prom tickets if anyone is interested. Fundraiser forms are in the NHS Library. Tickets will be $60 in March and will be $75 in April until the last purchase day, April 7th.
For more information, contact Nancy Bouliane at 936-825-4231 or email boulian@navasotaisd.org.

post_text:
We are currently experiencing power issues at John C. Webb Elementary. We have been in contact with Entergy and they have restored 2/3 power to building for the rest of the day. We will continue with our regular school day. Hot lunch will still be provided to all students as it is currently being cooked off campus and will be brought to Webb. Phones will be down for the entire day. In the case of an emergency a parent may call Central Office at 936-825-1108 or 936-825-4203 to get a message to the Webb campus.

At 4:15 p.m., Entergy will begin working to replace lines to restore full power. We are told work can be completed tonight and well be good for tomorrow. We will let you know if something changes.

Navasota Rattlers Boys Basketball
January 8 at 3:48 PM 路

Rattler Nation listen up: for district away games our high school boys are required to wear a button down shirt and tie to school and the game. If you have some things you would like to donate, we would gladly accept them. We are asking for help in collecting shirts, ties, pants, belts, anything that you would be willing to provide/donate to the team. We will keep the items in the basketball equipment room for players who need certain items. You can contact this page if you are interested in helping. You can also bring items to Mrs. Harris at the high school and she will get them to Coach Randolph. We are hoping to have items by Wednesday, January 15th. Thank you for your support.

post_text:
FAN INFORMATION FOR FRIDAY'S GAME:
4A Division I Area Playoff
Navasota vs. Midlothian Heritage
Friday, November 22 at 7:30 p.m. at Waco Midway.
Navasota is the HOME team!

Ticket prices:
Pre-sale tickets available at Navasota High School from 7:30 a.m. until 3:00 p.m. today. Student Tickets are $4.00 and Adult Tickets are $7.00. All tickets will be $8.00 at the stadium gate.

Here are a few stadium rules you should be aware of:
- Glass Containers & Bottles are not allowed in the stadium.
- Individual Coolers, Ice Chests and Large Food or Beverage Containers are not allowed in the stadium.
- Back Packs & Large Bags are not allowed inside stadium.
- No Outside Food or Drink allowed in stadium, including bottled water.
- Patrons Who Leave the Stadium will not be allowed to re-enter without paying. This includes patrons
with passes.
#ChampionsLiveHere #RattlerNation #WeAreNavasota

post_text: Mr. Wellmann is remembered for his assistance with traffic and crowd control at football games in the 70's and 80's, and his presence at many school functions giving fire truck rides as well as his help with Fire Safety instruction at our campuses. Navasota ISD extends their deepest condolences to the family of Mr. Charles Wellmann. #WeAreNavasota
shared_text:
Navasota Fire Department
October 18, 2019 at 7:01 PM 路

It is with a heavy heart that we announce that long time Senior Firefighter Charles Wellmann (Ret.) has lost his battle to cancer. Charlie spent 47 dedicated years of service to the department and the citizens of Navasota; starting as a volunteer before becoming a paid career firefighter. We ask that you please keep his family and FD family in your thoughts and prayers. Rest easy Brother, well take it from here.

Arrangements pending at this time.
